Please show me how, in similarly equipped situations where monks don't VERY MUCH outdamage warriors?    The simple fact is, you do significantly more damage in about every situation to warriors, and any claim to the contrary is asinine.<br>
<br>
Even IF you had the exact same weapons, which isn't the case in the natural progression of this game (ex. Primal Sword 13/20, fistwraps 15/20), monks STILL have flying kick, which compared to max kick skill (avg kick=28 points, my fuggin level 38 monk has better flying kicks than my 60 warrior with massive AA's kicks for).   Your weaopns skills are higher, AND you are a separate damage table.   You can NOT separate and dismiss these one at a time, because to do so is simply avoiding the aggregate bonus of having these.  Then, at EVERY level of play, dropped monk weapons are better than dropped warrior weapons, period.    <br>
<br>
