<br>
&quot;Getting aggro is not about doing the most damage, if it was warriors would use their most damaging weapons to hold aggro and smart ones do not.&quot;<br>
<br>
Outside of high end luclin encounters that I've never been involved in, which are in the process of being tweaked right now, high damage 2 hand weapons seem to hold an interesting amount of aggro when compared to their predecessors and the days gone by.<br>
<br>
Some procs and their effects have had their aggro causing properties changed over the past year or so (disease counters being one of them).<br>
<br>
So, while I understand what you're getting at, I think you need to keep in mind that things have changed a bit since Pre-Luclin. Damage IS a key component to maintaining aggro (always has been). And just when we think we have a handle on the game's combat mechanics, they're going to change them again.<br>
